{
  "stem": "12462.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was found guilty of crimes against humanity, because of his activities in Vienna, as the gau leader of Vienna, and particularly because of he making that statement of having-- which he never denied-- of having made the statement about the thousands and thousands of Jews who had been moved into the ghettos of the East-- 'I consider it a contribution to civilization.'",
      "word_count": 63
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He had also had a-- a conference with Hitler and somebody else, who I don't remember at the time, of which we had a document.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in that document, [CLEARS THROAT] Hitler had said, there's still 60,000 Jews in Vienna?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I want you to get rid of them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then, that document, we introduced.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, it didn't say where they were to be gotten rid of, or how, but they were, of course, pushed into some of the concentration camps, and most of them were killed.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "What was the sentence imposed on Schirach for his conviction on crimes against humanity?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "20 Years, which he served.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was two defendants got 20-year sentences, Schirach, and the defendant, Albert Speer.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Both of them served out their sentences.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Schirach wrote a book after a while, but it isn't a very impressive book, about his conversion and that he's-- why he was now against the Nazis, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Whereas, Speer wrote a very creditable book, after a while, which contains a pretty accurate statement of how things developed and how he felt.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He'd he was one of the defendants who really had a conversion and studied a lot while he was in Spandau prison during those 20 years.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[DRINKS WATER]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, he died some years back.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know how long back, but he died some years back.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
